radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated up to 11 mm and fluid-filled without evidence of oral contrast. Adjacent fat stranding is moderate. The lower lungs are clear. No evidence of a pleural or pericardial effusion. A few tiny hypodensities in the hepatic parenchyma may represent a cyst, hemangioma, or biliary hamartoma. The gallbladder is decompressed and normal. The pancreas and spleen are normal. The kidneys are normal and symmetric. No evidence of macroperforation or drainable fluid collection. No evidence of calcified stone in the appendix. No free fluid in the pelvis. No retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy.
